Here's a completely honest review.  I really enjoy mexican food and have ate at many mexican joints throughout the city.  Cesars failed to live up to my expectations.  I would say that this is like....the applebees of mexican restaurants.  The initial chips and salsa were great (it's hard to mess that up though).  I ordered 3 chicken tacos.  I was actually really surprised at how incredibly bland they tasted.  My margarita was fine, but it's not incredibly difficult to make a frozen margarita.  It almost seems like the food was an after thought (especially for the price I paid).  I would suggest checking out Azteca Grill right around the corner.  They don't serve margaritas but their foods is considerably better.  The wait staff was super nice and the service was great. I'm not upset about my experience or anything but I probably woln't come back. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ EDIT: In response to the owner.  It's not free advertising for Azeteca grill.  Their food just tastes way better.  They actually have a lot of really creative twists on mexican food that are surprisingly tasty.  I found the beans and rice at cesars to be lacking flavor.  The beans were kind of soupy.  Like I said...completely honest review.  I was just in the area and have no particular bias or attachment to your restaurant.  I just like eating out and I review places on google to keep people informed.

So the margs are good, but $13 for a "large" is a bit much since it is their smaller option, $17 for their "mega" which is 17.5 ounces aka their medium... it is pretty big, but just a bit pricey for the medium sized margarita... granted it got us both drunk and I would not need another. But there was also the $30-something pitcher (I feel like it was $32 but don't quote me). I did not see one while I was there so I have no idea if that is the best bargain or not.  My friend and I had the Mega marg and it was enough to get drunk for sure! They were not overly sweet and you can have your rim of salt or sugar if you choose. We chose against both. I had the orange flavor since the waiter said it was his favorite. I have also heard the guava is good. I wanted to try the mango, but it looked like a $2 surplus charge that I wasn't willing to commit to add on to the $17 that I was already spending on the 17.5 ounce marg.  Food was actually pretty good. My friend and I split the chicken fajitas. it came with a side of rice, small cup of guacamole, your choice of flour or corn tortillas, re-fried beans and rice. The veggies were DELICIOUS and the chicken wasn't too dry! I LOVED the flour tortillas. Definitely recommend.  Overall great experience, got drunk off the MEGA marg and had free soup, even got free shots from the waiter (always a plus), and the food was good! Bit steep on the price of the margs, that would be my only complaint.

This was our first visit to this restaurant. It will also be our last time. We went to see Blue Man Group and afterwards had reservations afterwards to eat here. I made the reservations for 730 but we arrived early. We got there about 655pm. I advised the hostess that I had reservations but we were a little early.  Now, in a normal circumstance, the answer would of been your table isn't ready yet, but we will start working on it. What we were greeted with was we can't seat you till predominately was there. There was 8 of us total and 6 was there. So then she said, well your table isn't ready. Ok, when will it be ready?  Well your reservations was for 730, so we can't seat you until then. Now, mind you, there are 2 sections to this place. There was space on both sides open. So after overhearing us talk about taking our business elsewhere, NOW our table was open.  After being seated, I still asked to speak with the manager. A young guy comes to the table and apologizes yo us for the misunderstanding. There was no misunderstanding,  we got there early and they refused to seat us. Plain and simple. So as I continue to look around, I notice this person that was the "manager" is serving food and waiting tables.  So I don't believe that was the manager at all that was sent to the table.  So now, we have a couple of people (one of the individuals who told me up front that they can't seat us) at our table apologizing for the mix up. Repeating the same phrase, "I know we got off to a bad start, but we are truly sorry".  Then as a friendly gesture, she brought over tequila shots. There's a saying a little too late and we were definitely pass that point. The margaritas are waaaayyyy over priced, and really aren't as good as I was hoping. The food was mediocre.  At the end, our bill was about $300.  Looking back, we should of left and gave that business to another restaurant.  Our waiter was fantastic, so no complaints there. Just the upfront crew was the thing that made this visit bad.   Now, on blue man groups website it says you are entitled to a free appetizer or dessert by showing your ticket stub. What they don't say is, it only includes 3 appetizers on there menu. We just wanted the guacamole and was told that wasn't an option. All in all bad experience, wouldn't go back and anyone ever asks, I will tell them try another place. This one wasn't worth it.
